</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32A651DFFEF762030A8FA4DBA7E56FA" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFEF762030A8FA4DBA7E56FA" blockId="9.[174,1232,1495,1682]" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">
All the enemies of the host wasp discussed above are usually named “parasites in the broad sense or parasitoids”, while the beetles in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF76203323FA6DB8F55679" box="[872,985,1527,1553]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Trichodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF76203323FA6DB8F55679" box="[872,985,1527,1553]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">Trichodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be considered as “nest destructors” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA14B67FFEF762031F9F98DB9B9565A" author="Zerova, M. D. &amp; Romasenko, L. P. &amp; Seryogina, L. Ya. &amp; Verves, Yu. G." box="[434,661,1559,1586]" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" refId="ref10699" refString="Zerova, M. D., Romasenko, L. P., Seryogina, L. Ya., Verves, Yu. G. Natural insect enemies of solitary bees of the fauna of Ukraine. - Kyiv: Veles, 2006. - 236 p. - Ukrainian: Ziрova М. D., Рoмaсiнko Л. P., Сiрьogiнa Л. Я., Viрviс Ю. G. Koмaki - pрiрodнi voрogi poodiнokik bdzoлiнik фauнi Ukрayнi." type="book" year="2006">Zerova et al., 2006</bibRefCitation>
). In the present study they penetrated two nests and ruined 38 cells of 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF762031F3F9A2B97B5639" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[440,599,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF762031F3F9A2B97B5639" box="[440,599,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">P. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nest destructors can cause huge damage in artificial nests, but in the present study they did not provoke considerable loss in the population of 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF762030E5F9E2BA6056F9" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[174,332,1655,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF762030E5F9E2BA6056F9" box="[174,332,1655,1681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">P. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
